A Visual Information Retrieval System.


EXECUTION ENVIRONMENT
=====================================
The codes were tested under MacOS, but should be also 
working under Linux system.


HOW TO INSTALL?
=====================================
You need python 2.5.1 (or newer version) and numpy 1.5.1 
(or newer), scipy 0.7.0, python image library 1.1.7 and cython 0.13 
(or newer).

Building by executing the script.
  $ sh install.sh

HOW TO RUN?
=====================================

1. Executing the visual information retrieval using color
  $ python main.py color

2. Executing the visual information retrieval using texture
  $ python main.py texture

3. Executing the visual information retrieval using both color and texture
  $ python main.py color texture

4. Plotting the scatter plot.
  $ python main.py scatter
